  "text": "A number of our features are based on prior polarity of words. As in the phrase-based system we too build off of prior work [CITATION_1] by using the DAL and augmenting it with Wordnet. However, we do not follow the earlier method but use it as motivation. We consider words with with a polarity score (using the pleasantness metric from the DAL) of less than 0.5 as negative, higher than 0.8 as positive and the rest as neutral. If a word is not directly found in the dictionary, we retrieve all synonyms from Wordnet. We then look for each of the synonyms in the DAL. If any synonym is found in the DAL, we assign the original word the same pleasantness score as its synonym. If none of the synonyms is present in the DAL, the word is not associated with any prior polarity. For the given data we directly found the prior polarity of 50.1% of the words. We find the polarity of another 8.7% of the words by using WordNet. So we find prior polarity of about 58.7% of English language words.",
